W. A. DOODY CO. et al. v. B. T. ADAMS & CO. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. June 20, 1903.) No. 1,232. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of Georgia.

Before PARDEE, McCORMICK, and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Finding no element of fraud or illegal preference in this case, the decree of the District Court is in all respects affirmed.
